---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Gian Trotta"
  description="Senior software engineer in Cleveland, Ohio. I've spent years making one very large website fast — now I do it for businesses whose owners I can shake hands with."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">About</h1>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I've spent years making one very large website fast — I'm a senior engineer at RVshare, an
        RV rental marketplace that serves millions of visitors. Speed, search visibility, and
        reliability are my day job.
      </p>
      <p>
        Now I'm doing the same for businesses whose owners I can actually shake hands with. I'm
        early in that journey — which means you get senior-level work, newcomer-level attention,
        and a developer genuinely hungry to make your project a portfolio piece.
      </p>
      <p>
        I live in Parma, Ohio with my wife and daughter. When your site loads instantly and shows
        up when someone asks Google — or ChatGPT — for a business like yours, that's the whole
        pitch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a
      href="/contact/"
      class="mt-10 inline-block rounded-md bg-flare-deep px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-porcelain hover:bg-flare"
    >
      Book a free 15-minute call
    </a>
  </section>
</Base>
